      <body>
         
         <head><emph>Peanuts</emph>, <date when="1962-05-23">23 May, 1962</date></head><!-- The title of the comic is its date. So change the two dates in this line, keeping them both in the proper format -->
         
         <div type="panelGrp" xml:id="Peanuts1962-05-23"><!-- Make sure that the value of this xml:id matches the idno from line 35 above. If there is a setting, weather, activities, or Bechdel test, tag them in the <div> with ana="" -->
            
            <cbml:panel n="1" characters="#CharlieBrown #LinusVanPelt"><!-- In each of the four panel blocks, record the characters that appear in the panel.   -->
               <note resp="#r-SDM" type="panelDesc">Charlie Brown and Linus are wearing baseball mitts and caps and are standing on a pitcher's mound. Linus is talking to Charlie Brown.</note><!-- Put your r-name from the taxonomy (e.g., #r-HJ, #r-DM, #r-AL, #r-KS) as the value of the resp attribute. Give a quick description of what happens in this panel -->
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#LinusVanPelt">I don't know what to do, Charlie Brown...</cbml:balloon><!-- Put in the character who is speaking. If there are no speech bubbles, remove this line. If it's a different type of bubble than a speech bubble, change the @type value.-->
               <!-- Add a second (or third!) <cbml:balloon> if there are multiple speech bubbles in a panel -->
               <!-- In addition to <cbml:balloon>, you also have the choice of <cbml:caption> for text that is not in a speech balloon (this will probably be incredibly rare in our corpus), <sound>, <figure> for music, or <floatingText type="diegetic">. -->
               <docDate>5-23</docDate><!-- Include the date as written in the comic. Move to a different panel if needed. Move it above the signature if need be. -->
            </cbml:panel>
            
            <cbml:panel n="2" characters="#CharlieBrown #LinusVanPelt" ana="#a-baseball"><!-- In panels 2, 3, and 4, also record the transition type according to McCloud using the tr- value from the taxonomy -->
               <note resp="#r-SDM" type="panelDesc">Charlie Brown and Linus are wearing baseball mitts and caps and are standing on a pitcher's mound. Linus is talking to Charlie Brown.</note>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#LinusVanPelt">I can't stand out there yelling, "C'mon Charlie Brown, you can strik him out!" When I really know that you can't...The more I think about it, the more it bothers me...</cbml:balloon>
            </cbml:panel>
            
            <cbml:panel n="3" characters="#CharlieBrown #LinusVanPelt" ana="#a-baseball">
               <note resp="#r-SDM" type="panelDesc">Charlie Brown and Linus are wearing baseball mitts and caps. Charlie Brown is standing on a pitcher's mound while Linus is walking away from the mound. Linus is talking to Charlie Brown.</note>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#LinusVanPelt">It's sort of a conscience problem</cbml:balloon>
            </cbml:panel>
            
            <cbml:panel n="4" characters="#CharlieBrown" ana="#a-baseball">
               <note resp="#r-SDM" type="panelDesc">Charlie Brown is wearing a baseball mitt and cap and standing on a pitcher's mound. Charlie Brown is talking to himself.</note>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#CharlieBrown">I never realized baseball was so ethical!</cbml:balloon>
               <docAuthor>SCHULZ</docAuthor><!-- Include Schulz's signature. If rendered differently, encode with a <hi rend=""> element. Move this to a different panel if need be. -->
            </cbml:panel>
            
         </div>
